<br>
I've read the entire thing.  It deconstructs a the most prominent criticisms to the Supreme Court's decision, and does so in a very convincing manner.  The only place where political outcomes are considered is in the final few paragraphs, which are dedicated to outlining the possible courses of action which the Court could have taken.<br>
<br>
I know its long, but if you are at all interested in the case, you really ought to give it a read.  And not just the closing paragraphs. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.visveres.myguilds.com/sigs/caledhon.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shehbahn>shehbahn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>No blood for oil!</span><br>  Posts: 683<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/7/03 6:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=470.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Stolen Elections!</span><hr size=1> Main problems are :<br>
<br>
a) i am no lawyer and certainly don't have the qualifications to assert the validity of a lot of the legal propositions<br>
<br>
b) my knowledge of the US constitution and legal system are fairly limited all things considered<br>
<br>
I have however read a fair amount of varied sources that seems to point to some malpractices. In any case : if the results of an election are ambiguous, the least that should be done regardless of the situation, is a recount. There is no other way to assert without any doubt of the constituency of a government. At least IMHO. If the electoral system does not have a trustworthy validation mechanism, i would say your democracy is in rather deep trouble. That's also why, when i see the piss poor jobs done with those electronic voting machines, i am indeed very suspiscious.<br>
<br>
S.<br>
