<br>
What is at issue here is whether the law was followed or not.  What more can you possibly ask of any government?  If every single contested vote was solved by a recount, nobody would ever be elected anywhere.  That is why Florida law is written the way it is.  There is a good long section of the article addressing exactly this subject, check it out.<br>
<br>
